solutions.content:
The idea is to do BFS using the given input array.

Every minute, just find and set the ones that are going to rot, to the current minute in the input array.
To illustrate the idea, consider how it would play out - 
Start by marking all fresh ones adjacent to the rotten ones with value 2 as 3.
Then, mark all fresh ones adjacent to the rotten ones with value 3 as 4.
Then, mark all fresh ones adjacent to the rotten ones with value 4 as 5.
...
Keep doing this until that are no more adjacent fresh oranges to rot.
Note: One can start timer at minute 2 as it's the time elapsed that matters. 

Time - O (N * Height)
Space - O (1) 
This offcourse assumes that the input can be modified.  

```
class Solution {
    public int orangesRotting(int[][] grid) {
        int time = 2;
        boolean moreToRot = true;
        while (moreToRot) {
            moreToRot = rotNextMinuteOnes(grid, time);
            if (moreToRot) time++;
        }
        return allRotten(grid) ? time - 2 : -1;
    }

    private boolean rotNextMinuteOnes(int[][] grid, int time) {
        boolean moreToRot = false;
        for (int i = 0; i < grid.length; i++)
            for (int j = 0; j < grid[0].length; j++)
                moreToRot = rotAdjacentIfJustRotten(grid, i, j, time) || moreToRot;
        return moreToRot;
    }

    private boolean rotAdjacentIfJustRotten(int[][] grid, int i, int j, int time) {
        if (grid[i][j] != time) return false;
        boolean right = rotIfFresh(grid, i, j + 1, time + 1);
        boolean bottom = rotIfFresh(grid, i + 1, j, time + 1);
        boolean left = rotIfFresh(grid, i, j - 1, time + 1);
        boolean up = rotIfFresh(grid, i - 1, j, time + 1);
        return right || bottom || left || up;
    }

    private boolean rotIfFresh(int[][] grid, int i, int j, int time) {
        if (i < 0 || i >= grid.length) return false;
        if (j < 0 || j >= grid[0].length) return false;
        if (grid[i][j] != 1) return false;
        grid[i][j] = time;
        return true;
    }

    private boolean allRotten(int[][] grid) {
        for (int i = 0; i < grid.length; i++)
            for (int j = 0; j < grid[0].length; j++)
                if (grid[i][j] == 1) return false;
        return true;
    }
}
