solutions.content:
**Note:** the same solution when runned at different times produce different runtimes,so it is adviced to not get disappointed about this ,rest assured this is a one of the best bfs solutions for this question.these submissions hold the the same code.
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/e0d98959-c60b-47a0-a907-570f43c598a4_1664644212.1830633.png)
if your solution is getting a high run time,here are some quick suggestions 
*  keep a variable which keeps count of ones 
*  keeping count of ones help in breaking the while loop as soon as all the oranges are rooten and prevents us from traversing the whole array in the worst case.
*  another use is to just check at the end if all the oranges are rotten or not.
**Approach**
*  if all zero or all two return 0
*  if all one return -1
* store the intially rotten tomatos in the queue so that we have starting point of infection, and apply bfs on them.
*  keep count of total unrotten tomatos and as soon as every tomato is wrotten terminate the loop.
* store the location of the rotten tomato and the time elepsed yet in the queue ,you can use different methods to do this,i just stored an array of size 3 in queue where i,j and time elepsed are stored respectively
*  rott the adjacent fresh oranges to these and store them in the queue.
*  store the time elapsed to reach previous fresh tomato + 1 for the current tomato in a variable ans.
*  when completed return ans.
**Code**
```
class Solution {
    int[][] arr;
    boolean inRange(int i,int j){//range validator
        return !(i<0||i>arr.length-1||j<0||j>arr[0].length-1);
    }
    public int orangesRotting(int[][] grid) {
        arr=grid;
        //possible movements
        int[] u={0,0,-1,1};
        int[] v={1,-1,0,0};
        Queue<int[]> q=new LinkedList<>();
        int zero=0,two=0,one=0;
 // ------------------------------------------------------------------------------            
        //count the zeros,twos and ones and store rotten tomatos into queue 
        for(int i=0;i<grid.length;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<grid[0].length;j++){
                if(grid[i][j]==0) zero++;
                else if(grid[i][j]==1) one++;
                else two++;
                if(grid[i][j]==2){
                q.add(new int[]{i,j,0});
                }
            }
        }
// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------     
        int ans=0;
        //optional as this check has no effect in long run
        int size=grid.length*grid[0].length;
        if(zero==size||two==size) return 0;
        if(one==size) return -1;
// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------        
        while(!q.isEmpty()){
                    size=q.size();
                    for(int k=0;k<size;k++){
                        int[] temp=q.poll();
                        int cost=temp[2];
                        for(int l=0;l<4;l++){
                            int a=temp[0]+u[l];
                            int b=temp[1]+v[l];
                            if(inRange(a,b) && grid[a][b]==1){//adding an adjacent fresh tomato into queue and rotting it.
                                q.add(new int[]{a,b,cost+1});
                                grid[a][b]=2;
                                ans=cost+1;//storing time elapsed.
                                one--;//reducing the count of fresh tomatos
                            }
                        }
                        if(one<=0) break;//if no fresh tomatos left break
                    }
                }
// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------            
        if(one!=0) return -1; //it is not possible to rott all tomatos
        return ans;    
    }
}
```

