# Optimised
```java
public int orangesRotting(int[][] grid) {
	int fresh_oranges = 0;
	int row = grid.length, col = grid[0].length;
	Queue<ArrayList<Integer>> queue = new LinkedList<>(); 
	for(int i = 0; i < row; i++) {
		for(int j = 0; j < col; j++) {
			if(grid[i][j] == 2) {
				ArrayList l = new ArrayList<>();
				l.add(i); l.add(j);
				queue.add(l);
			} 
			else if(grid[i][j] == 1) {
				fresh_oranges++;
			}
		}
	}

	if(fresh_oranges == 0) return 0;

	int minutes = -1; // because count of minute is starting from 0
	int[][] directions = {{-1,0}, {1, 0}, {0, -1}, {0, 1}}; // up down left right

	while(!queue.isEmpty()) {
		minutes++;

		int queue_length = queue.size();
		for(int i = 0; i < queue_length; i++) {
			ArrayList<Integer> coordinates = queue.poll();

			for(int[] direction: directions) {
				int x = coordinates.get(0) + direction[0];
				int y = coordinates.get(1) + direction[1];

				if(x < 0 || y < 0 || x >= row || y >= col || grid[x][y] == 0 || grid[x][y] == 2) continue; // continue if either out of range or apple is not fresh

				grid[x][y] = 2;
				ArrayList<Integer> l = new ArrayList<>();
				l.add(x); l.add(y);
				queue.add(l);
				fresh_oranges--;
			}
		}
	}
	if(fresh_oranges == 0) return minutes;
	return -1;
}
```

**Explanation**
BFS (Breadth First Search) is used in this method as we can think of this grid as a graph and these oranges connected. We need to find number of minutes including 0 required for all the oranges to get rotten.

The following steps are used:-
- count the number of fresh oranges present in the grid as well as put the row and column indices of those oranges that are rotten.
- if the number of fresh oranges is 0 it means that all the oranges are already rotten and we can just return 0.
- else we will iterate through all the entries in the queue and make adjacent oranges rotten.
- iterate and check for all four directions and if grid entry for those indices is 1 then enter them into queue as well as set them to 2. Don't forget to reduce the count of fresh oranges.
- at last check if fresh oranges count is 0 return minutes else return -1.

