This approach uses:
* a queue to track rotten oranges whose neighbors have not yet been checked
* a counter for the number of fresh oranges remaining in the grid
* an iteration counter (turns).

In each BFS iteration, the algorithm checks the neighbors of each rotten orange, and "rots" them, by placing the newly rotten orange location at the end of the queue, and decrementing the fresh count.  When the fresh count hits zero, the iteration counter is the answer.  If the queue is empty at the start of any iteration, then there are fresh oranges that will never rot, and we return -1.
```
class Solution {
    private static final int FRESH = 1;
    private static final int ROTTEN = 2;

    public int orangesRotting(int[][] grid) {
        final int m = grid.length;
        final int n = grid[0].length;

        // Scan for rotten oranges, and place in a queue.
        // Also count fresh oranges.
        int freshCount = 0;
        ArrayDeque<Integer> queue = new ArrayDeque<Integer>();
        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++)
            for (int j = 0; j < n; j++)
                switch (grid[i][j]) {
                    case FRESH: freshCount++; break;
                    case ROTTEN: queue.add(i * n + j); break;
                }
        if (freshCount == 0) return 0;

        // Use BFS to rot the oranges, and count the number of iterations
        int turns = 0;
        while (freshCount > 0 && !queue.isEmpty()) {
            turns++;

            // Pull each of the rotten oranges from the queue
            int queueSize = queue.size();
            for (int k = 0; k < queueSize; k++) {
                int ij = queue.pollFirst();
                int i = ij / n;
                int j = ij % n;

                // Find any adjacent fresh oranges, and rot them.
                // Decrement the fresh count, and queue the newly rotted orange.
                if (i > 0 && grid[i-1][j] == FRESH) {
                    if (--freshCount == 0) break;
                    grid[i-1][j] = ROTTEN;
                    queue.add((i-1) * n + j);
                }
                if (i < m-1 && grid[i+1][j] == FRESH) {
                    if (--freshCount == 0) break;
                    grid[i+1][j] = ROTTEN;
                    queue.add((i+1) * n + j);
                }
                if (j > 0 && grid[i][j-1] == FRESH) {
                    if (--freshCount == 0) break;
                    grid[i][j-1] = ROTTEN;
                    queue.add(i * n + j - 1);
                }
                if (j < n-1 && grid[i][j+1] == FRESH) {
                    if (--freshCount == 0) break;
                    grid[i][j+1] = ROTTEN;
                    queue.add(i * n + j + 1);
                }
            }
        }
        if (freshCount > 0) return -1;
        return turns;
    }
}
```

