solutions.content:
**Upvote if you like the post :)**

**What the problem actually says?**
`Given a binary tree root, a node X in the tree is named good if in the path from root to X there are no nodes with a value greater than X.`

**Visual Demonstration Below(Showing the Good Nodes) :-**
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/uploads/2020/04/02/test_sample_1.png)

**Intuition**:
* Firstly we will traverse in `PreOrder` manner.
* Keep a `maxi` variable passing in the recursion calls except for the parent node
* If at any time the current node value is `>=` the maxi seen so far then just update the maxi and increase the counter;  

**C++:**
```
class Solution {
public:
    int ans=0;
    void pre(TreeNode* root,int maxi){
        if(!root) return;
        if(root->val>=maxi){
            ans++;
            maxi = root->val;
        }
        pre(root->left,maxi);
        pre(root->right,maxi);
    }
    int goodNodes(TreeNode* root) {
        pre(root,INT_MIN);
        return ans;
    }
};
```
****
**Time Complexity**: **O(N)**
**Space Complexity**: **O(N)** for recursion stack space.
****

