1) Traverse the tree in preorder fashion.
2) For every node X, `max` is the maximum values so far from root to that node.
3) For the left and right childrens of X , `max` would be `max` of X and current value of node X itself.
4) At end of traversal of both left and right subtrees, add 1 to the total if current node is good Node. `((root.val >= max)?1:0) ` is used for that. 
