### JAVA CLEAN CODE SOLUTION 🙌🏼
* Logic of this question is that, we do a normal dfs ```pre order traversal```!
* And then check for good node at every node!!
* As the binary tree is not a BST, we have to keep track of maximum value node(previous) and send that to subtrees.
* Finally we return our total good nodes.
```
class Solution {

    public int goodNodes(TreeNode root) {
        return goodNodesHelper(root, Integer.MIN_VALUE);
    }

	//helper function
    private int goodNodesHelper(TreeNode root, int previous) {
        if (root == null) return 0;
        int nodes = 0;
        if (root.val >= previousMinimum) nodes += 1;
        return goodNodesHelper(root.left, Math.max(root.val, previous)) + 
			   goodNodesHelper(root.right, Math.max(root.val, previous)) + nodes;
    }
}

```

