# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
* All we want to do is to keep tracking of the maximum element in the branch till the current node, and if the current node value was greater than or equal to that max then we should increment our counter by 1. 
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
## count (root, mx, &cnt)
### return type and parameters 
1. it is a recursive function. 
2. it returns nothing (**void**)
3. root is a pointer for the current node. 
4. mx is the maximum value for the current branch, and it is passed by value, because we change it almost after each call. 
5. cnt is counter for all good node, and it is passed by reference. 
### base cases 
* we have mainly two base cases.
    1. if we have empty tree, so we just need to return from the function, and we will return 0 from the main function. 
    2. if we have reached a leaf.
        * at this point we just need to check if the leaf value was less than send mx, if yes then we will just return, otherwise we will increment counter by 1 then return. 
### recursive cases. 
* we just need to iterate over left subtree for each node, then traverse over the right one. 
```
    count(root->left, max(mx, root->val), cnt);  // left subtree
    count(root->right, max(mx, root->val), cnt); // right subtree
```  
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    * O(n) as we iterate over each node only once.  
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    * I do not use any extra space.  
# Code
```
/**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    #define DPSolver                      \
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); \
    cin.tie(NULL);                    \
    cout.tie(NULL)

void count(TreeNode *root, int mx, int &cnt)
{
    if (!root) // empty tree 
        return;
    if (root->val >= mx)
        cnt++;
    if (!root->left && !root->right) // leaf node. 
        return; 
    count(root->left, max(mx, root->val), cnt);  // left subtree
    count(root->right, max(mx, root->val), cnt); // right subtree
}

int goodNodes(TreeNode *root)
{
    DPSolver; 
    int cnt = 0;
    count(root, root->val, cnt);
    return cnt;
}
};
```

