# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. The approach is pretty straightforward--> Traverse through the tree whilst maintaining a parent node and a max variable.
2. Check whether the value of root is greater than parent as well as the max variable(as the question asks us to find out all the nodes within each path, which are greater than or equal to the greatest node anywhere before, in that path).
3. So if a node is greater than its parent and also max, it would imply that in the path UPTO THAT NODE, this node is greater than all the other preceding ones and hence is a GOOD NODE.
4. Increment the ans variable which has been created globally

