##### Declared a value maxx globally which is initialised to -10000 (-1*1e4) as the minimum value of the node is this only which keeps track of the maximum value of node that is traversed till the current node.
##### Now write the code of dfs (preorder) and checked if maxx value is less than or equal to value of current node then we will update the maxx value and store current maxx value in temp variable and increase the count by 1.
##### Then traverse to left child and right child and will return the count in the similar way. 
##### At last we will update the maxx value back to previous value as we are going back from that track.
##### And return the count.
```
class Solution {
    int maxx = -1*1e4;
public:
    int goodNodes(TreeNode* root) {
        if(root == NULL)
            return 0;

        int count = 0;
        int temp = maxx;
        if(maxx <= root->val){
            maxx = root->val;
            count++;
        }

        count += goodNodes(root->left);
        count += goodNodes(root->right);

        maxx = temp;
        return count;
    }
};
```

