solutions.content:
# Intuition
The Idea is we start to iterate from front first till we dont encounter different words in both sentences (or dont reach to end of either sentence )
. Now similarly Iterate from back with above conditions.

. If we have iterated through all words of either sentence the sentences will be similar

# Approach
We will implement the above intiution with Dequeue approach with following steps :
1. Store words from both sentences in two separate deques 
2. Now iterate from start in both deques and if words re same in both deques pop them else stop.
3. Similarly from backside
4. If either of deque is empty return true .

// Hope you understand this code well . Upvotes are appreciated . 


# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(m+n)

- Space complexity: O(m+n)
- Where m and n  are number of words in sentence 1 and sentence 2 respectively

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool areSentencesSimilar(string sentence1, string sentence2) {

        deque<string> s1 , s2;

        for(int i = 0 ; i< sentence1.length() ; i++)
        {
           int j = i;
           string temp;
           while(j<sentence1.length() && sentence1[j]!= ' ')
           temp.push_back(sentence1[j++]);

           i = j;
           s1.push_back(temp);
        }

        for(int i = 0 ; i< sentence2.length() ; i++)
        {
           int j = i;
           string temp;
           while(j<sentence2.length() && sentence2[j]!= ' ')
           temp.push_back(sentence2[j++]);

           i = j;
           s2.push_back(temp);
        }

        int i = 0 ;

        while(!s1.empty() && !s2.empty())
        {
            if(s1.front() != s2.front())
            break;

            s1.pop_front();
            s2.pop_front();
        }

        while(!s1.empty() && !s2.empty())
        {
            if(s1.back() != s2.back())
            break;

            s1.pop_back();
            s2.pop_back();     
        }

        return (s1.empty() || s2.empty());

    }
};
```

