solutions.content:
3 cases
- All matching words are at start of s1
- All matching words are at end of s1
- Matching words are present both at start and at the end

Approach:
- Left pointer counts the word matches from the start of s1
- Right pointer counts the word matches from the end of s1
- Sentences are similar if all words from s2 are used by pointers --> (sum of left count and right count)

```
class Solution {
    public boolean areSentencesSimilar(String s1, String s2) {

        // ensure sentence1 is longer
        if(s1.length() < s2.length()) return areSentencesSimilar(s2, s1);

        String[] w1 = s1.split(" ");
        String[] w2 = s2.split(" ");

        // count matching words in beginning
        int l=0;
        while(l< w2.length){
            if(w2[l].equals(w1[l])) l++;
            else break;
        }
        if(l== w2.length) return true;

        // count matching words at the end
        int r=0;
        while(r<w2.length){
            if(w2[w2.length-1-r].equals(w1[w1.length-1-r])) r++;
            else break;
        }
        return l+r==w2.length;
    }
}
```

