Intuition

- Let's reduce to the case where `sentence1` is longer than `sentence2`
- We want to split `sentence2` into two halves, `prefix` and `suffix`, that match `sentence1`
- For example, if `sentence1 = "a b c d"` and `sentence2 = "a c d"`, the prefix is `"a"` and the suffix is `"c d"`.

```
const areSentencesSimilar = (sentence1, sentence2) => {
  const array1 = sentence1.split(" ");
  const array2 = sentence2.split(" ");

  if (array1.length < array2.length) {
    return areSentencesSimilar(sentence2, sentence1);
  }

  // find the shared prefix between array1 and array2
  let prefixLength = 0;
  for (; prefixLength < array2.length; prefixLength++) {
    if (array2[prefixLength] !== array1[prefixLength]) {
      break;
    }
  }

  // the rest of array2 must be a suffix of array1
  const suffixLength = array2.length - prefixLength;
  for (let i = 0; i < suffixLength; i++) {
    if (array2[array2.length - 1 - i] !== array1[array1.length - 1 - i]) {
      return false;
    }
  }

  return true;
};
```

